<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Tower Format Converter</title>
<style>
html, body {
  height: 100%;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}
label {
  display: block;
}
textarea {
  resize: none;
}
#error-box {
  color: red;
}
.box-container {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-rows: 1em minmax(5em, 1fr) 1em minmax(10em, 3fr);
  grid-auto-flow: column;
  height: 100vh;
  padding: 8px;
  column-gap: 8px;
}
@media screen and (min-width:800px) {
  .box-container {
    grid-template-rows: 1em 1fr;
  }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
Paste tower blueprint strings into the base64 box to get decoded JSON
strings, or modify the JSON to get base64 codes to import.
  <div id="error-box"></div>
  <div class="box-container">
    <label for="base64">Base64 encoded:</label>
    <textarea id="base64"
              class="box"
              rows=12
              autocomplete="off"
              autocorrect="off"
              spellcheck="false"></textarea>
    <label for="json">JSON:</label>
    <textarea id="json"
              class="box"
              rows=12
              spellcheck="false"></textarea>
  </div>
  <script>"""REPLACE_JS_HERE"""</script>
</body>
</html>
